snippet.textDisplay: Five years ago, love touched me for the first time, a love so pure that in every glance, I glimpsed a future entwined with his. But time has unraveled us, and now he’s far away, across seas and skies, while I remain here, trying to move on. I’ve danced with others, laughed with friends, but no connection could echo the depth of what we had. Every time his eyes met mine, I saw forever, and now, all I have are shadows of what might have been. When he returns, even just a fleeting glimpse, I ache to vanish into him, to run away from this world and reclaim what was ours. But some things are not meant to be. A year has passed since he left, and with December’s cold breath comes the sharp sting of memories. It was always our month, our time, yet now it is a reminder of what I cannot hold. The streets we walked, the tea stall where time stood still—everything whispers of us, and I am weary of pretending to the world that I am whole. I am so afraid of being trapped in this grief, this endless yearning for what I cannot have. This time, when he comes back, I may not be here at all, for the weight of this loss threatens to swallow me whole. The love I lost is a song that haunts me, and I fear I will never find peace until I let go :)

snippet.textDisplay:
Safe with me, all the memories whispered,
Years slip away, yet you're still here,
A shadow in the silence, always near,
Though I long to set you free,
Your weight is a gravity I can't escape—

I could have wished for something more,
But what could I ever find?
When every echo, every trace of you,
Is all that fills my mind.
Each fading moment, still a fire,
That burns me whole, yet takes me higher,
For even the shadows you left behind
Are the only light I ever find.

Endless memories, like ghosts in my veins,
Defying time, defying change,
But not me.
What would we have been if you stayed?
What worlds would we have dared to claim,to shape?

I could have wished for something more,
But nothing else can feel this real,
When every glance, every silent touch,
Is everything I long to feel.
The weight of you, a ghostly grace,
A love that time cannot erase.
Though you're gone, though we're apart,
You’re still living in my heart.

It’s a hollow ache, a grief too deep,
A wound that time has yet to heal.
In every dream, I hear your voice,
A distant echo, a lost choice.
I reach for what is no longer mine,
But you're the only truth I find.

I could have wished for something more,
But no dream could ever compare,
When every thought, every piece of you,
Is all that I still wear.
Each memory, a scar so deep,
A love I’ll never let go, a love I’ll keep.
Though life moves on and fades away,
In my soul, you’ll always stay.

So here I stand, with love untold,
A heart that’s broken, but still bold.
I hold the pieces, torn and worn,
Of all we were, and all we mourn.
And in the quiet, in the pain,
You're the dream I’ll never explain.
